1
00:00:43,252 --> 00:00:47,047
Leave me alone, will ya?
You think you're so smart.

2
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:49,049
Would you stay still already?

3
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:51,051
What a geek!

4
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:53,053
- I'm not a geek!
- You're doing it wrong!

5
00:00:53,136 --> 00:00:55,055
- Shut up!
- You're doing it wrong.

6
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:57,140
- It doesn't go like that.
- Who asked you?

7
00:00:57,224 --> 00:01:00,185
- Who's your brother?
- You are, Stevie!

8
00:01:00,269 --> 00:01:02,813
You do it like this,
it'll open up in a fire,

9
00:01:02,896 --> 00:01:06,024
you'll get burned and die.

10
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:10,237
Let's go!

11
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:12,739
What d'you got, Adcox, a big deal?

12
00:01:12,823 --> 00:01:14,741
Medium deal, Captain.

13
00:01:14,825 --> 00:01:17,202
Hey, Brian, want to come along?

14
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:20,080
- Dad...
- Stephen, you've come a dozen times.

15
00:01:20,122 --> 00:01:22,624
Give your brother a chance.
What d'you say?

16
00:01:22,708 --> 00:01:24,751
We'll be back in a minute.
How about it?

17
00:01:24,793 --> 00:01:26,628
- Sure!
- Come on!

18
00:01:37,097 --> 00:01:40,392
- Pull the cord, Brian!

19
00:01:40,434 --> 00:01:42,769
1545 Idylwild.

20
00:01:57,576 --> 00:01:59,620
- Give it a yank, a good pull.

21
00:01:59,661 --> 00:02:02,206
You've gotta get
these cars outta the way.

22
00:02:02,289 --> 00:02:04,625
- Give it another yank!

23
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:25,354
Well, there it is,
right over there. See it?

24
00:02:38,367 --> 00:02:40,327
Okay.

25
00:02:40,369 --> 00:02:42,329
You stay
near the truck now.

26
00:02:43,330 --> 00:02:45,290
That doesn't look too bad.

27
00:02:45,332 --> 00:02:47,751
Drop two lines
and hold the squad.

28
00:02:47,835 --> 00:02:49,795
Everything I own in the
whole world is up there.

29
00:02:49,837 --> 00:02:52,548
All my stuff's up there!

30
00:03:00,806 --> 00:03:03,767
Adcox! Ladder up!

31
00:03:03,851 --> 00:03:05,853
Hey, that's your
old man up there, Brian.

32
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:31,336
Nice grab, Captain!

33
00:03:33,463 --> 00:03:36,175
Take it easy.
You'll be okay.

34
00:03:47,728 --> 00:03:50,105
We got it!
Come on.

35
00:04:12,503 --> 00:04:13,754
Dad!

36
00:04:13,837 --> 00:04:16,965
Hold on, Adcox.
Is that a gas line?

37
00:04:17,758 --> 00:04:19,593
- Dad!

38
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:59,818
Hey, Brian!
Brian McCaffrey, got some I.D.?

39
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:02,696
Hey, Willie!
I'll give you I.D.!

40
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:04,740
- The littlest McCaffrey!
- How you doin'?

41
00:06:04,823 --> 00:06:08,076
Hot off the presses, boys!
Station assignments!

42
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,120
Hey, McCaffrey!
Station assignments!

43
00:06:10,204 --> 00:06:12,289
Why don't you hold onto
that for me, huh?

44
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:15,042
Something wrong
with my eyesight?

45
00:06:15,125 --> 00:06:17,044
You really trying
this fireman thing again?

46
00:06:17,127 --> 00:06:20,797
- Quitting once wasn't good enough?
- It's in the blood.

47
00:06:20,881 --> 00:06:22,799
- Is that right?
- Willie, you owe me a brew!

48
00:06:22,883 --> 00:06:24,885
Hold on!
I'm talking to the fire chief!

49
00:06:24,927 --> 00:06:27,346
Let's look and see
what else was in your blood.

50
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:29,389
I always looked forward
to getting these.

51
00:06:29,431 --> 00:06:33,810
- You hold onto those, huh?
- Whoa! I got station 17!

52
00:06:33,894 --> 00:06:38,524
"Aspen Snowmobile Tours.
Brian McCaffrey, Sales. "

53
00:06:38,565 --> 00:06:40,859
It didn't offer the growth
and challenge that I needed.

54
00:06:42,736 --> 00:06:44,863
"Cattle Drive Mobile Log Cabins. "

55
00:06:44,905 --> 00:06:47,574
- That was in your blood six months?
- The coffee sucked.

56
00:06:47,658 --> 00:06:51,537
"Brian's Sound Spectrum,
Direct Hi-end Stereo Sales. "

57
00:06:51,578 --> 00:06:53,664
This is your own company.
This was a big step, huh?

58
00:06:55,874 --> 00:06:58,168
I was ahead of my time, Willie.

59
00:06:58,252 --> 00:06:59,628
McCaffrey!

60
00:06:59,711 --> 00:07:02,673
What's the matter with you?
Aren't you even curious?

61
00:07:04,716 --> 00:07:07,553
Engine 115, right?

62
00:07:13,183 --> 00:07:15,769
How'd you know, you prick?
These are supposed to be sealed.

63
00:07:15,811 --> 00:07:18,063
Lucky guess.

64
00:07:18,105 --> 00:07:22,276
And a case of Scotch to the captain
at station assignments.

65
00:07:22,359 --> 00:07:24,278
You crooked son-of-a-bitch!

66
00:08:13,076 --> 00:08:14,995
Make us proud, guys!

67
00:08:15,078 --> 00:08:16,997
McCaffrey, that's
my cousin's company.

68
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,999
Come on!

69
00:08:26,131 --> 00:08:28,967
Calm down, Mrs. Vaitkus.

70
00:08:32,888 --> 00:08:35,307
Mrs. Vaitkus, please, calm down.

71
00:08:37,976 --> 00:08:40,145
McCaffrey, I think it's a box,
or a 211, at least.

72
00:08:40,187 --> 00:08:43,690
- Just give me one minute.
- Hurry, we can't miss this one!

73
00:08:45,859 --> 00:08:47,861
- Hey.
- Hi, Jen.

74
00:08:47,945 --> 00:08:51,406
- I see your grandma's still-
- Yeah, she still hates you.

75
00:08:54,535 --> 00:08:58,455
- You look great.
- Thanks. How long you been in town?

76
00:08:58,539 --> 00:08:59,540
Four months.

77
00:08:59,581 --> 00:09:01,959
- Oh, really.
- But I, uh...

78
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:04,336
I've been really busy
at the academy.

79
00:09:04,378 --> 00:09:06,797
I graduated today.

80
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,882
I can see that.

81
00:09:08,966 --> 00:09:11,051
So what have you been up to?

82
00:09:11,093 --> 00:09:14,805
Well, uh...
I work at city hall, actually.

83
00:09:14,888 --> 00:09:18,433
No kidding? That's great!

84
00:09:18,517 --> 00:09:21,728
So...
I don't know what-

85
00:09:25,649 --> 00:09:29,903
Maybe you and I could...
could get together for a beer.

86
00:09:29,945 --> 00:09:32,072
A beer?

87
00:09:34,241 --> 00:09:36,159
Beer... that's-

88
00:09:36,243 --> 00:09:39,580
It's funny. You're acting
like I just saw you last week.

89
00:09:39,621 --> 00:09:42,374
When I haven't seen you
in what... six years?

90
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:46,920
You son-of-a-bitch!

91
00:09:46,962 --> 00:09:49,006
Don't want ya overheatin', Brian!

92
00:09:49,089 --> 00:09:51,341
I'll give you overheatin'!

93
00:09:58,015 --> 00:10:00,559
Easy, man. I don't have
time for this bullshit.

94
00:10:00,642 --> 00:10:03,478
Well, you've certainly matured.

95
00:10:07,232 --> 00:10:10,068
Well, it's nice to know
we can still be friends.

96
00:10:13,113 --> 00:10:16,825
Come on, Brian.
We got a fire to go to.

97
00:10:18,202 --> 00:10:20,746
Engine 17,
your pressure's fine.

98
00:10:20,787 --> 00:10:22,748
Get out of the way here,
please.

99
00:10:22,789 --> 00:10:25,083
Officers, you're standing around
with your thumb up your asses.

100
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:27,085
- Where you going?
- I'm a fireman.

101
00:10:27,169 --> 00:10:28,504
Go!

102
00:10:31,131 --> 00:10:33,050
Need a second lead-out?

103
00:10:33,091 --> 00:10:35,052
What the fuck are you
talking about?

104
00:10:35,093 --> 00:10:36,720
- Get out of here!
- Brian!

105
00:10:39,431 --> 00:10:41,308
This is the
real shit, man!

106
00:10:41,391 --> 00:10:43,310
The real thing!

107
00:11:33,777 --> 00:11:35,696
Well, what do we got here?

108
00:11:35,779 --> 00:11:37,698
A fireman's costume, huh?

109
00:11:37,781 --> 00:11:40,492
Where'd you rent it?

110
00:11:40,576 --> 00:11:43,662
Thanks for coming to
my graduation today, brother.

111
00:11:43,704 --> 00:11:45,664
You're a real
inspiration to me.

112
00:11:45,706 --> 00:11:49,001
I'm sorry, man.

113
00:11:49,084 --> 00:11:53,505
You're really ready to fight
fire this time, huh, Brian?

114
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:58,385
It just doesn't work on you,
little brother.

115
00:11:58,468 --> 00:12:01,346
- I'll see you around.
- Not likely.

116
00:12:01,388 --> 00:12:05,058
You see, that's where
you're wrong already.

117
00:12:05,142 --> 00:12:07,686
I talked to
Chief Fitzgerald.

118
00:12:07,728 --> 00:12:11,064
He decided maybe you shouldn't be
way on the other side of town...

119
00:12:11,106 --> 00:12:13,066
where I'd never
get to see you.

120
00:12:13,108 --> 00:12:15,068
Starting tomorrow,
you're going to be...

121
00:12:15,110 --> 00:12:18,071
with the toughest company
in the city.

122
00:12:18,113 --> 00:12:20,616
17... my company.

123
00:12:23,076 --> 00:12:25,412
One case of Scotch, Brian?

124
00:12:25,454 --> 00:12:27,956
Man, you're gettin' cheap
in your old age.

125
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:31,335
Get outta here, girls.

126
00:12:31,418 --> 00:12:36,057
You should learn not to box
when the 17's on the job.

127
00:13:05,994 --> 00:13:08,789
Hey, Inspector Rimgale,
she's all yours.

128
00:13:25,639 --> 00:13:27,599
Hey, give me a shot
of that, will ya?

129
00:13:45,826 --> 00:13:47,828
Hey, Shadow.

130
00:13:47,870 --> 00:13:50,205
So, you got a cause there?

131
00:13:52,249 --> 00:13:54,168
Mice with matches.

132
00:13:57,337 --> 00:13:59,298
Well, the glory boys
are going to have to...

133
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:02,301
wait a few days on this one.

134
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:11,727
Sean?

135
00:14:11,810 --> 00:14:12,978
Sean!

136
00:14:15,314 --> 00:14:17,941
Hey, buddy.
What's goin' on?

137
00:14:20,944 --> 00:14:22,863
It's Uncle Brian.

138
00:14:24,239 --> 00:14:26,200
You'll remember this.

139
00:14:26,241 --> 00:14:28,202
Spinach?

140
00:14:28,243 --> 00:14:31,705
We don't need no
stinkin' spinach!

141
00:14:31,747 --> 00:14:33,499
- Mom! Mom!
- Hey...

142
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:35,709
Hey, what's-

143
00:14:35,792 --> 00:14:37,544
Come here. It's okay.

144
00:14:37,586 --> 00:14:40,380
- Hello?
- Yeah?

145
00:14:41,882 --> 00:14:44,843
- Brian...
- Hey, Helen.

146
00:14:44,885 --> 00:14:47,095
God, I'd about
written you off.

147
00:14:47,179 --> 00:14:49,598
I know, well-

148
00:14:49,681 --> 00:14:51,600
So, uh...
What's goin' on?

149
00:14:51,683 --> 00:14:53,602
- Can I come in for a second?
- Sure.

150
00:14:54,561 --> 00:14:56,563
- How you doin'?
- Okay.

151
00:14:56,605 --> 00:14:58,565
Good to see you.

152
00:14:59,983 --> 00:15:01,902
So that's Sean, huh?

153
00:15:01,944 --> 00:15:03,820
Geez, he's a little giant now.

154
00:15:03,904 --> 00:15:08,200
You'd be surprised
what a few years can do to a kid.

155
00:15:08,242 --> 00:15:11,286
- Remember your Uncle Brian?
- No.

156
00:15:11,370 --> 00:15:13,747
You don't remember him?

157
00:15:13,789 --> 00:15:17,918
Hey, Sean-man.
Where's your daddy today?

158
00:15:21,380 --> 00:15:25,259
Uh... Stephen's not
staying here anymore.

159
00:15:27,261 --> 00:15:29,471
He moved out last April.

160
00:15:35,352 --> 00:15:37,396
I'm sorry, Helen, I, uh-

161
00:15:37,437 --> 00:15:41,775
You guys should try picking up
the phone once in a while.

162
00:15:54,872 --> 00:15:56,790
Hey!

163
00:15:59,626 --> 00:16:01,461
Hey.

164
00:16:01,503 --> 00:16:05,549
I, uh...
talked to Helen.

165
00:16:09,636 --> 00:16:12,097
I thought Dad's boat
was finally retired...

166
00:16:12,139 --> 00:16:14,099
to the old family graveyard.

167
00:16:16,518 --> 00:16:19,146
Don't you worry about
falling out of this thing?

168
00:16:21,815 --> 00:16:23,734
I've gotta tell you,

169
00:16:23,817 --> 00:16:26,361
I love what you've
done with the place.

170
00:16:26,445 --> 00:16:28,614
Yeah, it's comin' along.

171
00:16:33,952 --> 00:16:35,621
You want a beer?

172
00:16:35,662 --> 00:16:37,915
Yeah, why not?

173
00:16:37,998 --> 00:16:41,335
What, you been rippin' off
fire stations again?

174
00:16:41,376 --> 00:16:43,337
Just some old stuff...

175
00:16:43,378 --> 00:16:45,964
that Adcox gave me that
the department was gonna throw out.

176
00:16:46,006 --> 00:16:48,467
But it's good enough
for this tub.

177
00:16:48,509 --> 00:16:50,177
What is this?

178
00:16:50,260 --> 00:16:53,055
"Iron Butterfly,"
"Cream"?

179
00:16:53,138 --> 00:16:55,891
You gotta be kidding! This isn't
an actual operating 8-track!

180
00:16:55,974 --> 00:16:57,893
What do you want, Brian?

181
00:16:57,976 --> 00:17:00,229
What are you doin' here?

182
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:06,902
I wanna know why you messed
with my station assignment.

183
00:17:06,985 --> 00:17:09,279
I mean, does this
really have to be...

184
00:17:09,363 --> 00:17:11,782
one of those big brother,
little brother...

185
00:17:11,865 --> 00:17:14,368
you broke my G.I. Joe and
I'm still pissed games?

186
00:17:14,451 --> 00:17:16,537
Man, how do you do it, huh?

187
00:17:16,578 --> 00:17:18,622
How d'you keep
coming up with...

188
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:20,666
new and amazing ways
to fuck up?

189
00:17:20,707 --> 00:17:22,668
I mean, that Scotch bullshit?

190
00:17:22,709 --> 00:17:26,046
Am I really supposed
to believe you came home...

191
00:17:26,129 --> 00:17:28,340
because you felt heartstrings
moan for the family biz?

192
00:17:28,382 --> 00:17:30,342
You were bankrupt!
The scary thing is...

193
00:17:30,384 --> 00:17:33,846
you probably coulda
got away with it for awhile.

194
00:17:33,887 --> 00:17:35,848
Hang back a little bit
at the fires-

195
00:17:35,889 --> 00:17:37,933
You know the drill.

196
00:17:38,016 --> 00:17:41,061
The only problem is,
that in this job...

197
00:17:41,103 --> 00:17:43,063
there's just no place to hide.

198
00:17:43,146 --> 00:17:46,066
It's not like having
a bad day selling log cabins.

199
00:17:46,149 --> 00:17:48,819
You have a bad day here,
somebody dies.

200
00:17:48,902 --> 00:17:52,114
And that's just not
fucking good enough.

201
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:57,119
You know something?

202
00:17:57,202 --> 00:17:59,121
I must've told myself
a million times...

203
00:17:59,204 --> 00:18:01,373
I didn't even want
to be a damn fireman.

204
00:18:01,415 --> 00:18:04,042
Look, I know I quit
the academy before.

205
00:18:04,084 --> 00:18:07,254
- And I know how you must've felt.
- Oh, you do?

206
00:18:07,296 --> 00:18:09,256
You know how I felt?

207
00:18:09,339 --> 00:18:11,758
I gotta do this, Stephen.

208
00:18:13,886 --> 00:18:15,804
I need to know.

209
00:18:15,888 --> 00:18:19,725
Yeah, I think you're
going to find out, Brian.

210
00:18:22,603 --> 00:18:25,647
Try not to be late
tomorrow, huh?

211
00:18:47,169 --> 00:18:50,005
Give me a break, huh!

212
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:55,761
Shit!

213
00:18:55,802 --> 00:18:57,763
Come on, damn it!

214
00:19:11,735 --> 00:19:13,779
Oh, shit!

215
00:19:15,113 --> 00:19:17,533
- My car wouldn't start!
- What are you doin', man?

216
00:19:20,953 --> 00:19:22,871
Atta boy!

217
00:19:24,581 --> 00:19:26,500
Damn!

218
00:19:30,796 --> 00:19:33,340
Come on, man.
You can make it!

219
00:19:42,808 --> 00:19:45,561
Well, Baby McCaffrey,
how you doin'?

220
00:19:45,644 --> 00:19:47,479
How you doin', John?

221
00:19:50,858 --> 00:19:53,360
Hey, Axe,
you know this rug rat?

222
00:19:53,402 --> 00:19:55,571
Know him?
I practically raised him.

223
00:19:55,654 --> 00:19:58,782
He never calls.
He never writes.

224
00:19:58,866 --> 00:20:00,826
I'm Brian.

225
00:20:00,868 --> 00:20:03,412
I'm sorry.

226
00:20:18,260 --> 00:20:21,054
All right!
Garment factory.

227
00:20:21,138 --> 00:20:25,058
Shake and bake, boys!
I think we got a barbecue.

228
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:28,979
Got yourself a hot one
first time out, kid.

229
00:20:45,370 --> 00:20:47,706
Oh, yeah, this is
gonna taste like shit.

230
00:20:47,748 --> 00:20:50,250
- All right, let's go!
- Shit!

231
00:20:53,504 --> 00:20:57,633
I hate it when we gotta
fucking go look for it.

232
00:20:57,716 --> 00:21:00,636
Call in a box, Otis.
We're gonna need some back-up.

233
00:21:00,719 --> 00:21:03,013
Brian, inch-and-a-half.

234
00:21:03,096 --> 00:21:05,641
Get the high-rise jet.

235
00:21:14,024 --> 00:21:17,611
- These moments do try me.
- Be gentle now, Axe.

236
00:21:20,614 --> 00:21:22,533
Holy shit!

237
00:21:28,121 --> 00:21:30,040
Coming through!

238
00:21:36,296 --> 00:21:38,340
Hey, Probie,
how about it, huh?

239
00:21:44,471 --> 00:21:46,390
- You ready?
- Yeah.

240
00:21:47,808 --> 00:21:50,310
You're doin' it wrong.

241
00:21:52,354 --> 00:21:55,482
Stay beside me.
I mean, right beside me.

242
00:21:55,524 --> 00:21:58,360
Come on, man.
Kick it in.

243
00:21:58,443 --> 00:22:00,112
Get down!

244
00:22:04,449 --> 00:22:06,368
Show time!

245
00:22:19,423 --> 00:22:21,175
Got it!

246
00:22:41,236 --> 00:22:44,907
- Let's take it from the side.
- No, let's hit it head-on!

247
00:22:44,990 --> 00:22:48,577
It's gonna flash on us, Bull.
We gotta back out!

248
00:22:48,660 --> 00:22:51,079
She'll steam on us a little,
but she won't flash.

249
00:22:51,163 --> 00:22:53,582
Here comes your water.

250
00:22:57,878 --> 00:22:59,755
Here it comes!

251
00:23:12,559 --> 00:23:14,436
All right,
let's go for the throat!

252
